  "title": "Load instantsearch with hierarchicalFacetsRefinements",
  "body": "Hello!\r\n\r\nI am trying to initialize instantsearch with some pre checked filters. Basically I have a hierarchical menu with categories, and when the user visit for example /music/genre/rock i wanna make the \"rock\" value checked by default. I've tried this but with no luck: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/830\r\n\r\nMy code looks like this:\r\n```\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n\t...\r\n\tsearchParameters: {\r\n\t\thierarchicalFacetsRefinements: {\r\n\t\t\t'music.genre': ['Rock']\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\tfacetingAfterDistinct: true,\r\n\t\thighlightPreTag: '__ais-highlight__',\r\n\t\thighlightPostTag: '__/ais-highlight__'\r\n\t}\r\n});\r\n```\r\nand the hierarchical menu:\r\n```\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n\tinstantsearch.widgets.hierarchicalMenu({\r\n\t\tcontainer: '#genres',\r\n\t\tseparator: ' > ',\r\n\t\tsortBy: ['count'],\r\n\t\tattributes: ['music_hierarchical.genre.lvl0', 'music_hierarchical.genre.lvl1', 'music_hierarchical.genre.lvl2'],\r\n\t})\r\n);\r\n```\r\nWithout this part everything works fine:\r\n```\r\nhierarchicalFacetsRefinements: {\r\n\t'music.genre': ['Rock']\r\n},\r\n```\r\nBut when I add that part I am getting:\r\n**Cannot read property 'separator' of undefined at i._getHierarchicalFacetSeparator (instantsearch-preact.min.js?ver=1.2.0:4)**\r\n\r\nDoes anybody know what is going on here? Any help is very appreciated.",
